<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="390" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,829,964]" pageId="2" pageNumber="390">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,451,829,855]" pageId="2" pageNumber="390">Diagnosis (instars II–III).</emphasis>
Within 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sharp" authorityYear="1880" box="[538,645,829,855]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="395" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Bidessini">Bidessini</taxonomicName>
, larvae of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Young" authorityYear="1967" box="[756,912,829,855]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Hemibidessus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="390" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[756,912,829,855]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="390">Hemibidessus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are characterized by the following combination of characters: A3 lacking a ventroapical spinula (
<figureCitation box="[698,779,865,891]" captionStart="FIGURES 10–16" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1895,1919]" captionTargetBox="[179,1408,183,1859]" captionTargetId="figure-18@10.[179,1408,181,1871]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 10–16. Hemibidessus conicus (Zimmermann, 1921), instar II: (10) left antenna, dorsal aspect; (11) right antenna, ventral aspect; (12) left maxilla, dorsal aspect; (13) right maxilla, ventral aspect; (14) right mandible, dorsal aspect; (15) labium, dorsal aspect; (16) labium, ventral aspect. Numbers and lowercase letters indicate primary setae and pores, respectively.Asterisk indicates secondary seta. AN: antenna; LA: labium; MN: mandible; MX: maxilla. Scale bars = 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6882994" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6882994/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="390">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
); legs elongate (ratio L3/HW&gt; 3.20); femur and tibia with natatory setae (
<figureCitation box="[320,388,901,927]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–9" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[174,1413,181,1867]" captionTargetId="figure-20@9.[174,1413,181,1872]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 4–9. Hemibidessus conicus (Zimmermann, 1921), instar III: (4) head, dorsal aspect; (5) head, ventral aspect; (6) abdominal segment VIII, dorsal aspect; (7) right metathoracic leg, posterior aspect; (8) left metathoracic leg, anterior aspect; (9) right urogomphus, dorsal aspect. CO: coxa; FE: femur; FR: frontoclypeus; PA: parietal; NS: natatory setae; PT: pretarsus; TA: tarsus; TI: tibia; TR: trochanter; UR8: urogomphal primary seta UR8. Scale bars = 0.15 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6882992" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6882992/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="390">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
); secondary setae on dorsal margin of protarsus (
<figureCitation box="[935,1003,901,927]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–9" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[174,1413,181,1867]" captionTargetId="figure-20@9.[174,1413,181,1872]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 4–9. Hemibidessus conicus (Zimmermann, 1921), instar III: (4) head, dorsal aspect; (5) head, ventral aspect; (6) abdominal segment VIII, dorsal aspect; (7) right metathoracic leg, posterior aspect; (8) left metathoracic leg, anterior aspect; (9) right urogomphus, dorsal aspect. CO: coxa; FE: femur; FR: frontoclypeus; PA: parietal; NS: natatory setae; PT: pretarsus; TA: tarsus; TI: tibia; TR: trochanter; UR8: urogomphal primary seta UR8. Scale bars = 0.15 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6882992" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6882992/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="390">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
); urogomphus elongate (ratio U/HW ˃ 2.70), with numerous secondary setae (
<figureCitation box="[590,658,937,963]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–9" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[174,1413,181,1867]" captionTargetId="figure-20@9.[174,1413,181,1872]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 4–9. Hemibidessus conicus (Zimmermann, 1921), instar III: (4) head, dorsal aspect; (5) head, ventral aspect; (6) abdominal segment VIII, dorsal aspect; (7) right metathoracic leg, posterior aspect; (8) left metathoracic leg, anterior aspect; (9) right urogomphus, dorsal aspect. CO: coxa; FE: femur; FR: frontoclypeus; PA: parietal; NS: natatory setae; PT: pretarsus; TA: tarsus; TI: tibia; TR: trochanter; UR8: urogomphal primary seta UR8. Scale bars = 0.15 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6882992" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6882992/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="390">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
); primary seta UR8 inserted apically on urogomphomere 2 (
<figureCitation box="[1334,1402,937,963]" captionStart="FIGURES 4–9" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1896,1920]" captionTargetBox="[174,1413,181,1867]" captionTargetId="figure-20@9.[174,1413,181,1872]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 4–9. Hemibidessus conicus (Zimmermann, 1921), instar III: (4) head, dorsal aspect; (5) head, ventral aspect; (6) abdominal segment VIII, dorsal aspect; (7) right metathoracic leg, posterior aspect; (8) left metathoracic leg, anterior aspect; (9) right urogomphus, dorsal aspect. CO: coxa; FE: femur; FR: frontoclypeus; PA: parietal; NS: natatory setae; PT: pretarsus; TA: tarsus; TI: tibia; TR: trochanter; UR8: urogomphal primary seta UR8. Scale bars = 0.15 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6882992" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6882992/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="390">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
